Package: axue-translate
Version: {{VERSION}}
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Architecture: {{ARCH}}
Depends: xclip, xdotool, libx11-6, libxext6, libice6, libsm6, libfontconfig1, libssl3 | libssl1.1
Recommends: libnotify4
Installed-Size: {{SIZE}}
Maintainer: AxueTranslate Maintainers <noreply@example.com>
Homepage: https://github.com/cwr-1219/AxueTranslate
Description: Hotkey-driven AI translation tool for Linux desktops
 AxueTranslate is a desktop utility that lets you press a global hotkey to
 translate the currently selected text (or the whole input) using a Large
 Language Model API (DeepSeek, Xiaomi, or any OpenAI-compatible endpoint),
 then automatically pastes the translation back into the focused window.
 .
 This package provides the X11 build of AxueTranslate, written in C# /
 Avalonia 11. It ships as a self-contained .NET 8 binary so no system
 dotnet runtime is required.
 .
 Wayland sessions are not supported (XTest-based input simulation requires
 an X11 server). On Wayland desktops, log out and pick the X11/Xorg session
 before launching.
